article.headline: Indiana St. 75, Illinois St. 73
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. -- Harry Marshall hit a field goal with 1-second left on the clock in overtime to give Indiana State a 75-73 victory over Illinois State on Sunday. Marshall had 24 points and nine rebounds for Indiana State (5-19, 3-10 Missouri Valley) while Jay Tunnell led the team with 28 points and 12 rebounds for a double-double. He had eight 3-pointers. Osiris Eldridge tied the game at 73 for Illinois State (19-5, 8-5 Missouri Valley) with a pair of free throws with 21 seconds left in overtime. Eldridge finished with 13 points and ten rebounds for a double-double. Champ Oguchi led the Redbirds with 19 points and 11 rebounds, including five 3-pointers, for his own double-double. Lloyd Phillips added 14 points. The game was tied at 25 at half time and both teams shot 35 points in the second period to go into overtime with a tie 65 score. Jordan Printy fouled out for Indiana State.
